> FOOD TREND RIFF COMIN' IN HOT. We took the traditional sandwich (bread, meat, chili, carrot, pickly things, mayonnaise, and magic), lost the bread (been eating soooo many stress carbs), and threw it in our favorite eating vessel, THE BOWL. Once we looked at said bowl, filled with saucy beef, carrot, pickles, and spicy mayo, we threw back in some carbs because...life can be stressful. Hello, lime rice!

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1%unit}, 1 ¼ cups water
(2 ¼ cups for 4 servings), and a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to
a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Peel and finely chop @garlic{3%cloves}(peeled and finely chopped).
Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered).
Trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); slice
crosswise into thin half-moons. Halve, peel, and medium dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced).
Trim, peel, and grate @carrots{3%oz}(peeled and grated).

== Sriracha Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{1%unit}, as much @sriracha{2%unit} as
you'd like, a pinch of @garlic{pinch}, and a squeeze of lime juice.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings),
a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and juice from 2 lime wedges.

== Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{1%unit}, remaining garlic, and @sugar{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4 servings).
Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
about ~{5%minutes}. Stir in @soy sauce{2%unit}. Turn off heat; taste and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a fork and stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tbsp}; divide between
#bowls{}.

Arrange beef, grated carrot, and pickled cucumber on top. Top with a squeeze
of lime juice. Drizzle with sriracha mayo.